   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>I also agree! Some suggestions:

* take the openhatchery username, so people can visit <a href="https://facebook.com/openhatchery">https://facebook.com/openhatchery</a> to get 
to our page (openhatch is unfortunately already taken)
* be consistent about publishing blog entries there as they come out (the January release notes 
haven't been posted yet, for example)
* add the IRC channel information and encourage people to come say hi in the About section
* add more contact info. Add the blog and bugtracker sites and maybe the mailing list.
* revise the Company Overview to reflect the current direction for OpenHatch.
* get some screenshots up to populate the Photos section, and pictures from meetups, if those 
happen.
* occasionally write status updates reminding people about the weekly meetings, and highlighting 
important new features (the training missions would be perfect).</pre>
